<div class="pd-fileexplorer-documentation">

	<section id="overview">
		<h2 class="doc-section">Overview</h2>
		<p>
			<code>PDFileExplorer</code> is a file browser component that combines a tree view for directories
			and a table view for files. It supports navigation, selection, context menus, and file operations.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Tree navigation</strong> - Browse folder hierarchy</li>
			<li><strong>Table view</strong> - View files with details</li>
			<li><strong>Context menus</strong> - Right-click actions</li>
			<li><strong>File operations</strong> - Copy, move, rename, delete</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section id="quick-start">
		<h2 class="doc-section">Quick Start</h2>

		<DocExample Title="Basic File Explorer"
					AnchorId="basic-explorer"
					Code="@_example1Code"
					Language="razor"
					DemoStyle="min-height: 150px;">
			<DemoContent>
				<p class="text-muted p-3">
					See the full PDFileExplorer demo for interactive examples.
					The file explorer requires a data provider implementing the file system interface.
				</p>
			</DemoContent>
			<Description>
				<p>
					The file explorer combines <code>PDTree</code> and <code>PDTable</code> components
					with a custom data provider to enable file browsing.
				</p>
			</Description>
		</DocExample>
	</section>

	<section id="parameters">
		<h2 class="doc-section">Parameters</h2>
